    "John Trapp": "For an everlasting covenant .] Circumcision, the outward sign of it, was temporary, and changeable into baptism; but the covenant of grace, thereby then, and by baptism now, sealed up unto us, is eternal; being established and ratified. by the death of the Testator, \"by the blood of the Arch-shepherd\". { #Heb 13:20 } Here it must be considered { a } that there is a twofold covenant:\n7. For an everlasting covenant.] Circumcision, the outward sign of it, was temporary, and changeable into baptism; but the covenant of grace, thereby then, and by baptism now, sealed up unto us, is eternal; being established and ratified. by the death of [v_Heb_13_20] the Testator, \"by the blood of the Arch-shepherd\". {#Heb 13:20} Here it must be considered {a} that there is a twofold covenant:\n7. Is the Lord among us? ] As if that could not be, and they athirst. But he is most present when he afflicts. \"He knows our souls in adversity.\" { #Ps 31:7 }\nVer.\n7. Is the Lord among us?] As if that could not be, and they athirst. But he is most present when he afflicts. \"He knows our souls [v_Psa_31_7] in adversity.\" {#Ps 31:7}\nVer.",
